cs.CR, cs.GT, cs.SI, cs.CY, cs.PF

The paper deals with privacy threats and location privacy, which are common topics in the computer security (cs.CR) sub-category. The use of game theory to model the decision-making of both the user and the company suggests that the paper could also belong to the game theory (cs.GT) sub-category. The paper also mentions the use of real-data from a testbed, which suggests that it could belong to the social and information networks (cs.SI) sub-category. The paper deals with economic rational decision-making, which suggests that it could belong to the cybernetics (cs.CY) sub-category. Finally, the paper mentions the profit of the company, which suggests that it could belong to the performance (cs.PF) sub-category.
